<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 24 at 4:27PM CST  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WILL IMPACT EAST CENTRAL TALLADEGA...
NORTHWESTERN RANDOLPH...SOUTHEASTERN CALHOUN...SOUTHWESTERN CLEBURNE
AND NORTHEASTERN CLAY COUNTIES THROUGH 515 PM CST...
At 427 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Oxford Lake to near Munford. Movement was east
at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Anniston, Oxford, Heflin, Munford, Anniston Regional Airport, Oxford
Lake, Mount Cheaha, Hollis Crossroads, Lake Cleburne, Dearmanville,
Camp Mac, Micaville, Chalafinnee, Ironaton, Lake Chinnabee, and Camp
Sequoyah.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
